 54‚Üí *
 55‚Üí * ```
 56‚Üí * The tt_utoff value is never equal to -2**31, to let 32-bit clients negate it without overflow.
 57‚Üí * Also, in realistic applications tt_utoff is in the range [-89999, 93599] (i.e., more than -25 hours and less than 26
 58‚Üí * hours); this allows easy support by implementations that already support the POSIX-required range
